    <div class="feature-hero animate-fade-up">
      <span class="section-tag">📚 Learn</span>
      <h1>Animal <span class="gradient-text">Education</span></h1>
      <p>Understanding animals, their behaviour, and how we can coexist responsibly.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="info-grid animate-fade-up delay-100">
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-icon">🐕</div>
        <h3>Understanding Stray Animals</h3>
        <p>Stray animals are often abandoned pets or born on the streets. They face hunger, disease, and danger from traffic daily. Most strays are naturally gentle and simply need food and water. Community feeding programs can dramatically improve their quality of life. Spaying and neutering helps control population humanely.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-icon">🤝</div>
        <h3>Safe Interaction with Animals</h3>
        <p>Always approach slowly and let the animal come to you. Avoid sudden movements or loud noises. Don't touch an animal eating or sleeping. Never pull tails or ears. Teach children to be gentle with animals. If an animal shows signs of aggression, back away slowly without turning your back.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-icon">⚖️</div>
        <h3>Animal Welfare Laws in India</h3>
        <p>The Prevention of Cruelty to Animals Act (1960) protects animals from unnecessary suffering. Harming or killing animals is punishable by law. The Wildlife Protection Act (1972) safeguards endangered species. Abandoning a pet is a criminal offence. Animals used in experiments must be treated humanely.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-icon">🦁</div>
        <h3>Wildlife Protection</h3>
        <p>India has a rich biodiversity with over 500+ wildlife sanctuaries and national parks. Never feed wild animals — it disrupts their natural diet. Report poaching or endangered animal sightings to forest authorities. Respect wildlife corridors and migration paths. Support conservation efforts through awareness and donations.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-icon">🏥</div>
        <h3>Common Animal Diseases</h3>
        <p>Rabies is the most common zoonotic disease — vaccination is critical. Distemper affects dogs and is highly contagious. Feline leukemia is a serious concern for stray cats. Mange (skin disease) is treatable with proper medication. Regular deworming keeps animals healthy.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-icon">🌱</div>
        <h3>Building an Animal-Friendly Community</h3>
        <p>Set up community water bowls during summer. Organize neighbourhood feeding programs. Create awareness about animal welfare in schools. Report animal abuse to authorities. Support local shelters through volunteering or donations. Adopt, don't shop.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

